## 07 · Tab Visibility

Each tool, stack, and panel in the browser sidebar has a hide toggle (–/✕). When the admin activates this toggle for an item, the native Revit tab belonging to that item's source add-in is suppressed for users loading this profile. This is the only mechanism for controlling add-in tab visibility — there is no separate list or checklist.

### Mechanism

- **Default** — all add-in tabs visible. Admin explicitly opts in to hiding per item.
- **Hide toggle** — inline –/✕ control on every row in the Available Tools, Stacks, and Panels sections of the browser sidebar. Active state (✕) is visually distinct — amber styling. Inactive state (–) is neutral.
- **Effect** — at runtime, the extension reads which items are marked hidden and suppresses the corresponding add-in tabs via pyRevit. Only add-in tabs are in scope — native Revit tabs (Architecture, Structure, etc.) are never hidden.
- **Stored in profile** — hide state per item is written to the profile JSON on export and applied consistently across all users loading that profile.

> **Scope:** Tab autohide is confirmed possible via pyRevit — existing source available as reference implementation. Add-in activate/deactivate via `.addin.inactive` renaming is out of scope for this version. Only tab visibility is managed at this time.

