## 11 · Known Limitations

This is an open source tool targeting a community that is already accustomed to managing Revit fragility. The following limitations are acknowledged and accepted as part of the design philosophy. Community contributions are the primary mitigation path for most of these.

| Area | Limitation | Mitigation | Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| Revit version scope | Supported from Revit 2024+. Profiles built on newer Revit versions may not work on older installs — CommandIds may differ or be absent | Profile `min_version` written automatically at export and surfaced in the Profile Selector. Users loading mismatched profiles are warned; tool failures surface version metadata. Use at own risk — no further handling provided. | Accepted |
| PostCommand scope | `PostCommand` queues execution asynchronously and may not cover every add-in command — requires POC confirmation per Revit version | Validated at record time — invalid CommandIds rejected with clear message; version-pinned testing per release | Verify First |
| Add-in support scope | Only add-ins that register commands correctly as ribbon items are supported — commands not visible in Revit's shortcut dialog cannot be captured | By design — non-registering add-ins are an add-in quality problem; they fail cleanly at record time with a clear message | Accepted |
| Ribbon API fragility | Version-sensitive; may break on new Revit releases | Version-pinned testing; community patches per Revit release | Accepted |
| Panel and tool colors | Color input is hex code only — no color picker widget. Admin must know or look up their hex values. | Simpler implementation, no widget dependency. Revit API and pyRevit ribbon API both confirmed to support color. Hex is sufficient for the target user. | Confirmed |
| Tab autohide | Native Revit API support for hiding add-in tabs confirmed via pyRevit | Confirmed possible via pyRevit — existing source available as reference. Scoped to add-in tabs only; native Revit tabs are not hidden. | Confirmed |
| Profile updates | No dynamic update — users must re-add the updated `.json` profile file via the Profile Selector to receive changes from the admin | Accepted by design; document clearly in README | Accepted |
| Recording API | `ComponentManager.ItemExecuted` via `adwindows.dll` is not an officially supported Autodesk API — behaviour may change without notice on Revit updates | Widely used in the community; version-pinned testing per Revit release; community patches expected | Verify First |
| Recording mode | Tool activates normally when admin clicks it during recording — execution cannot be cancelled without meaningful added complexity | Accepted by design — minor side effect in an admin-only session; documented in setup guide | Accepted |

