## 12 · Open Questions

The following questions are unresolved and should be addressed before development begins.

- **Q01 — Tech stack** *(Resolved)* Python / pyRevit extension. Wider contributor pool, pyRevit hide tool available as reference, stronger training data for AI-assisted development.

- **Q02 — Admin tool architecture** *(Resolved)* The Tab Creator runs inside Revit as a pyRevit tool, accessed from the Add-ins tab — it is both the profile management surface and the editor. Profile Selector is a separate standalone app for users, running outside Revit. They share a profile file format but are otherwise independent.

- **Q03 — Multiple Revit versions** *(Resolved)* The Profile Selector includes a Revit version dropdown populated from detected local installs. The user selects which install they are configuring — this determines which `.addin` manifest paths are targeted. Profiles incompatible with the selected version are shown greyed out. Switching versions in the dropdown updates the active context throughout the app.

- **Q04 — Panel and tool colors** *(Resolved)* Both panel background color and tool accent color are confirmed supported via Revit API and pyRevit ribbon API. Color input is hex code — no color picker widget.

- **Q05 — Tab autohide** *(Resolved)* Confirmed possible via pyRevit. Existing source available as reference implementation.

- **Q06 — Load order** *(Resolved)* Not applicable. Add-in activate/deactivate via `.addin.inactive` renaming is out of scope for this version. Tab visibility is managed at runtime via pyRevit; load order does not affect this mechanism.

- **Q07 — Installer format** *(Resolved)* pyRevit extension distribution. No custom installer required.

- **Q08 — Prefix character** *(Resolved)* Eliminated. The recording mechanism captures tool identity directly via CommandId at click time. No prefix convention is needed. The concept no longer exists in the workflow.

- **Q09 — Tool name and identity** *(Resolved)* RESTer — Revit Environment Standardization Tool. The name is the tool. No associated commercial product.

- **Q10 — Initial Revit version scope** *(Resolved)* Revit 2024+. This is the declared minimum supported version. Profile min_version metadata is written automatically at export time. Users may attempt to use profiles on older versions at their own risk — version mismatch is surfaced in the Profile Selector and at runtime on tool failure, but is not blocked.

- **Q11 — PostCommand viability confirmation** *(Open)* `UIApplication.PostCommand(RevitCommandId)` is the committed execution mechanism. The POC must confirm it works reliably for both native Revit commands and properly-registered add-in commands across all target Revit versions (2024+). This is the first thing to build and test.

- **Q12 — Stack name field** *(Resolved)* Stack names are shown in the Tab Creator for internal admin reference only. They help the admin keep stacks straight while building the profile. Not surfaced to users at any point — stacks have no visible label in the Revit ribbon.

